      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a constitutional principle that protects fundamental rights from government interference, regardless of the procedures followed. It has been a crucial tool for expanding civil liberties, allowing courts to strike down laws that infringe upon deeply rooted rights like privacy and personal autonomy. This doctrine has been instrumental in safeguarding individual freedoms against government overreach, ensuring a baseline of personal liberty for all citizens.",
      "source": "target",
