      "content": "Landmark cases like *Griswold v. Connecticut* and *Roe v. Wade* are prime examples of substantive due process protecting personal liberties. *Griswold* established a right to marital privacy, while *Roe* recognized a constitutional right to abortion, demonstrating the Court's role in protecting deeply personal decisions. These rulings show how the doctrine has been used to defend fundamental rights against legislative intrusion.",
